## 🔄 Workflow Overview

### 1. Branching Strategy
Feature branches are created from `main`.

Example:
git checkout -b feature/add-high-score

---

### 2. Pull Request Flow
- Push changes to a feature branch
- Open a Pull Request (PR)
- CI/CD pipeline runs automatically
- Merge into main after validation

---

### 3. CI/CD Pipeline

Workflow file:
.github/workflows/docker-publish.yml

#### Pipeline Steps:
1. Checkout repository
2. Login to GitHub Container Registry (GHCR)
3. Generate Docker image tags
4. Build Docker image
5. Push image to GHCR

---

## 🐳 Docker Images

Published to:
ghcr.io/<your-username>/<your-repo>

### Tags:
- main → latest stable build
- pr-# → pull request builds
- v1.0.0 → release version
- latest → latest release

---

## ▶️ Run the Application

docker pull ghcr.io/<your-username>/<your-repo>:main
docker run -p 8080:80 ghcr.io/<your-username>/<your-repo>:main

Open:
http://localhost:8080

